{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "13", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "16", "M": "18", "S": "48"}}, "news": [{"title": "NGT halts all constructions inside Ghaziabad city forest", "para": "The National Green Tribunal has ordered the Ghaziabad district magistrate to stop illegal construction. This directive came after a plea alleged damage to Sai Upwan city forest. The tribunal noted that arguments from the applicant remained uncontroverted. Sai Upwan is a notified city forest under Ghaziabad Master Plans. The next hearing for this significant environmental matter is scheduled for September 16.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/ngt-prohibits-illegal-constructions-in-ghaziabads-sai-upwan-city-forest/132369366?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1232827/132369366.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "UP-RERA issues guidelines for refund of excess GST collected from homebuyers", "para": "UP-RERA has clarified the procedure for refund of excess GST collected from allottees in registered real estate projects. It has directed promoters to collect GST only at rates notified by the government.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/rera/up-rera-implements-refund-guidelines-for-excess-gst-charged-to-homebuyers/132367215?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-43148/132367215.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "rera"}, {"title": "SC freezes bank accounts of Parsvnath Developers, directors; issues warrants against its officials", "para": "The Supreme Court froze Parsvnath Developers' bank accounts and issued warrants.  This action followed a twenty-year struggle by senior citizens for their homes.  The court criticized Haryana authorities for failing to enforce RERA orders.  This case highlights concerns about the Real Estate Act's effectiveness.  The court expressed grave concern over regulatory authority inaction and potential collusion.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/supreme-court-freezes-accounts-of-parsvnath-developers-over-homebuyer-rights-violation/132369424?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-279710/132369424.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}